events.title: Uruguay Drought
events.description: Since the beginning of 2018, there has been a significant reduction in availability and access to water due to a deficit caused by a lack of rain, which has been further affected by the La Nina phenomenon in the South American region.

events.title: Central Asia Heatwave
events.description: During the middle of February, temperatures averaged above normal over a wide area of Central Asia, including eastern Kazakhstan, northern Kyrgyzstan, Turkmenistan, and much of Afghanistan.

events.title: Kadovar Volcano, Papua New Guinea
events.description: The first confirmed historical eruption at Kadovar began around mid-day local time on 5 January, according to witnesses.

events.title: Southeast Asia Agricultural Burning
events.description: Every January through March, vast numbers of small fires spring up across the countryside in Southeast Asia. Those months usually bring cool, dry weather—perfect conditions for burning.

events.title: Iceberg A68A
events.description: An iceberg about the size of Delaware has split off from the Larsen C ice shelf.

events.title: Sheveluch Volcano, Russia
events.description: Sheveluch is one of the largest and most active volcanoes on Russia’s Kamchatka Peninsula.

events.title: Sinabung Volcano, Indonesia
events.description: Mount Sinabung in Indonesia erupted on 21 May at 09:48 UTC (04:48 local time) and killed seven people in the nearby village of Gembar. The volcano is still erupting, pouring ash 3 km into the sky.

events.title: Dukono Volcano, Indonesia
events.description: During 16 and 19-22 March, ash plumes from Dukono rose to altitudes of 1.5-2.4 km (5,000-8,000 ft).

events.title: Iceberg D15B
events.description: D15B calved from D15 in January 2016.

events.title: Iceberg D15A
events.description: D15A calved from D15 in January 2016.
